changelog.comment: Initial entry. Reviewer 1 checked crosslinks, factual correctness, and reaction description, UniProt ID yet unreviewed. Reviewer 2 replaced CXSMARTS with normal SMARTS.

reactions.description: TdaE relies on its substrate as electron donor (rather than NAD(P)H) for O2 activation and covalent flavin-oxygen adduct formation. Then, TdaE incorporates both O2-derived oxygen atoms into the substrate most likely via transient FlN5OO and FlN5O species, thereby breaking the CoA thioester bond and epoxidizing the tropone ring.
